      "name": "Ohio State University",
      "location": "Columbus, Ohio",
      "region": "Midwest",
      "archetype": "The Big Ten Powerhouse — Engineering, Business, Medicine, and the Reindustrializing Heartland",
      "oneSentenceSummary": "Ohio State combines massive scale, elite engineering and medical research, Big Ten athletic culture, and a rapidly transforming Columbus economy anchored by the Intel semiconductor investment into one of the most comprehensive public university experiences in America.",
      "pipeline": "Approximately 46,000 undergraduates, one of the five largest universities in the country. Ohio State is nationally recognized for Engineering (aerospace, chemical, civil, computer science, electrical, industrial, materials science, mechanical, nuclear, welding), Business (Fisher College), Medicine, Nursing, Agriculture, Data Analytics, and Public Policy. Major recruiters include Intel, Honda, JPMorgan Chase, Nationwide, L Brands, Cardinal Health, Boeing, Lockheed Martin, Epic Systems, Deloitte, EY, PwC, and Ohio State's own massive academic medical center.",
      "hiddenPathway": "The Intel New Albany semiconductor fabrication investment — one of the largest private investments in Ohio history — has fundamentally changed the value proposition of an Ohio State engineering degree in the last three years, creating a direct pipeline into the reshoring of American chip manufacturing.",
      "institutionalSecret": "While Ohio State's size and football culture dominate its public image, its true institutional strength is the breadth of elite programs hidden inside that scale — one of the largest academic medical centers in the country, a top-20 engineering college, and a business school with deep Midwest corporate placement, all coexisting inside the same 46,000-student ecosystem.",
      "theRoom": "Located in Columbus, a city that has undergone one of the most significant economic transformations in the Midwest over the past decade — anchored by the Intel semiconductor project, a growing fintech and insurance sector (Nationwide, JPMorgan's Midwest hub), and a fast-growing logistics and healthcare economy.",
      "lifestyle": "Massive Big Ten spirit, football-centric on fall Saturdays, Greek-heavy, and increasingly shaped by Columbus's rapid growth into a genuine tech-adjacent city rather than a purely college-town economy.",
